---
import { site } from '../data/site';
---
<p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="lead">Effective date: April 26, 2026</p>

<section>
  <p>This privacy policy applies to the OpenWords app (hereby referred to as "Application") for mobile devices, created by Dzina Maslouskaya (hereby referred to as "Service Provider") as a free service. The Application does not require account registration and does not transmit personal data to the Service Provider.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Data Collection</h2>
  <p>The Service Provider does not collect, store, or process any personal data from users of the Application.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>The Application integrates third-party SDKs that collect anonymized usage and diagnostic data on the Service Provider's behalf:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Firebase Analytics (Google LLC)</strong> — collects anonymized usage data including app events, session information, device model, and OS version. This data is used solely to understand how the app is used and to improve it.</li>
    <li><strong>Firebase Crashlytics (Google LLC)</strong> — collects crash reports including stack traces, device model, OS version, and app version at the time of a crash. This data is used solely to identify and fix bugs.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The Application also relies on Google Play Services (Android) and Apple frameworks (iOS), which may independently collect device information subject to their own privacy terms: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>The Application does not knowingly collect any personal data from children under the age of 13. The third-party services integrated into the app collect only anonymized, non-identifiable usage and diagnostic data.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>Since the Service Provider does not collect or store any user data, there is no user data at risk on the Service Provider's end.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated effective date.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></p>
</section>

